I don't think it is at all wrong to say that Uber Wizards might have a slightly jaded opinion simply because we've been out of the &quot;old&quot; rat race for awhile.  I don't think any of you think your perfect.  I also don't think any of you SHOULD be implying that we know better simply because we are there, and you are not.  2 years ago, I was making the same assumptions about losing track of the old game.  And to an extent, I agree with it.  If that is insulting, I'm sorry.  But it has been a long time since I wasn't doing raid after raid night after night and the monotony makes me forget the old things.  I don't think it is too much to admit that.  Both sides are looking at the extremes.  There is a compromise here.  Yes, we did our time.  Yes, our opinions might be a bit skewed in todays game.  But in no way should we be chastised that our enhancements were the ones that made the cut.  Just keep pushing.  It is all you can do.<br>
